Class OrderedPair<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,B extends java.lang.Comparable<B>>

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<OrderedPair<A,B>>

    public final class OrderedPair<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,B extends java.lang.Comparable<B>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<OrderedPair<A,B>>
    Represents an ordered 2-tuple, either one or both of the elements can be null. This class is immutable if and only if both underlying elements are immutable. In this class, a null element is considered to be "lesser" than a non-null element. For example, the pair (null, "Hello") is lesser than ("Hello", "World").
